        <td width="500" align="center" class="resize">
        	<table width="500" align="center" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" class="resize">
            <tbody><tr>
            <td width="100%" align="left" valign="top" style="font-family:'Century Gothic', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size:18px; line-height:22px; color:#010101; padding-top:20px;"><strong>PRACTITIONER, SUPPORT WORKER AND LOGISTICAL ROLES</strong></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
            <td width="100%" height="20" align="center" valign="top"><img src="http://www.ncsthechallenge.org/images/staffing/Images/ncstc_hr_290914.jpg" width="500" height="20" border="0" style="display:block;" class="resize100p"></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
            <td width="100%" align="left" valign="top" style="font-family:'Century Gothic', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size:14px; line-height:20px; color:#010101; padding-bottom:20px;">
            	<p><strong>Practitioner Roles</strong> (Non-residential) Use your drama, media, enterprise, photography, music or sport expertise to deliver skill-building workshops, and help your team to use this skill to interact with their community.</p>

<p><strong>Support Worker Roles</strong> (Semi-residential) Work closely with a young person with additional needs, ensuring that they participate to their full potential and helping them to intergrate with the rest of the team.</p>

<p><strong>Logistics Officer Roles</strong> (Non-residential) Assist with the logistical management of different weeks of the programme, managing relationships with key partners and young people.</p>

<p><strong>More information on our seasonal roles can be found on our website.</strong></p>


                <p><a href="http://ncsthechallenge.org/summer-staff-testimonials"_blank"><img src="http://www.ncsthechallenge.org/images/staffing/Images/NCSthechallengeYoung_People_discussion_point.JPG" alt="Click to watch full clip" width="430" height="370" border="0" style="display:block;" class="resize100p"></a></p>
            </td>
            </tr>
            </tbody></table>
        </td>
        </tr>
